## Commit

```bash
git add -A
git commit -m "fix(ui): v2.38.1 Operation ID column + Analysis deep-link + raw-output scroll fix

Three post-ship v2.38.0 verification fixes — Kent reported all three
from the same session.

OPERATION ID VISIBILITY: v2.38.0 Analysis view references 'operation_id
found in Logs → Operations or URL' but the Operations table showed only
Started/Label/Status/Duration/Model/Calls/Feedback — no UUID anywhere,
not even in the expanded detail. Fix adds an 'ID' column between
Started and Label showing operation.id first 8 chars with click-to-copy
full UUID and a 1.5s check-mark flash. Expanded detail row gains an
Identifiers block listing full Operation ID + Session ID as copyable
monospace pills plus a 'Deep-dive in Analysis →' button. Colspan on
the detail row bumped 7 → 8 to match the new column count.

ANALYSIS DEEP-LINK: the Deep-dive button writes {template_id:
'operation_full_context', params: {operation_id}} to sessionStorage
['deathstar_analysis_deeplink'] and dispatches CustomEvent
'navigate-to-tab' with {tab: 'Analysis'}. App.jsx listens for the
event and calls setActiveTab('Analysis'). AnalysisView on mount reads
and clears sessionStorage, pre-populating selected + paramValues.
Matches the existing event-bus pattern used by 'open-session-output'
in LogTable.jsx — no new infrastructure. Operator clicks Deep-dive on
any op row and lands in Analysis with the template picked and the
operation_id pre-filled, one keystroke from Run.

RAW-OUTPUT SCROLL FIX: clicking '+ Raw output log' or changing a
filter chip/keyword in SessionOutputView caused the outer Operations
table to scroll, shoving the expanded row up or down out of view.
Reported exactly as 'when pressing raw output log you get bumped
down, or logs get's bumped up, same with any filters chosen in raw
log'. Root cause: Element.scrollIntoView() ascends through every
scrollable ancestor, so bringing the raw-output bottom into view also
scrolled the Operations container. Fix replaces the bottomRef +
scrollIntoView pair with a linesContainerRef + direct scrollTop =
scrollHeight write on the lines div. scrollTop does NOT propagate to
ancestors — same UX (autoscroll to newest line on load/filter
change) but the outer page stays put.

Tests: 10 structural guards in tests/test_analysis_deeplink_wiring.py
lock in the ID column header, copyId/openInAnalysis helpers,
Identifiers block + Deep-dive button presence, colspan=8, scoped
autoscroll (linesContainerRef + scrollTop), scrollIntoView removal,
App.jsx listener, AnalysisView useCallback import, and deep-link
sessionStorage round-trip (read + removeItem + late-arrival listener).

No schema changes. No new Settings keys. No new dependencies. Three
files touched: LogTable.jsx, App.jsx, AnalysisView.jsx."
git push origin main
```

